history.text: Hello, it is so good to see that Gal Gadot was cast in this movie!
I thought Gal Gadot really outdid herself for this. It was amazing!
I didn't expect Robin Wright to be in the movie though but I'm glad she was.
It sure was.  It also the first time a female directed a live action comic book superhero movie.  I thought that was pretty cool.
Yes, me too.  She is just lovely and a wonderful actress.
Do you think the critics were fair?
Yes, and they were mostly positive.  I don't see how someone could say that it was sloppy, though...
How about you?
I agree. I think it was one of the most inspiring and entertaining movies I've seen in a long time.
Me too!  I hope they make a sequel.
I would buy them all!
I missed how the Amazons were created by Zeus.
Honestly I don't recall that story either. Another reason to watch it again!
I enjoyed the love story aspect as well.
I did too. I don't even recall seeing a face put to Zeus?
No, I didn't either.   I thought we would see him.
Do you usually watch Superhero movies?
Yes but this was one of the best I've seen!
It really was a lot less grim than I expected.  I also enjoyed the "fish out of water" aspect.
Yeah it was interesting to me that they focused on the godlike aspects with her and Ares, but still kept it modern with the war.
Definitely.  I liked learning more about her weaponry (the lasso and sword) as well!
That lasso was one of my favorite things.
What did you think about the chief chemist?
He was awful! He was just as bad as the general. How about you?
Yes, but the villains were fun to watch, I thought.
The training sequence in the beginning was cool too!
It was fun to watch the war scenes during the climax of the movie. They did so great with the graphics
Yeah the training scenes got me hyped for sure!
Yes, they don't really bother me in such movies.
It was also satisfying when Wonder Woman chose to help the humans even though she say that they could be so evil.
*saw*
I know she's supposed to exemplify everything a woman can be, but I couldn't help but notice her armor was hardly anything at all and still remained perfect haha
Haha!  Well, take care.  It was nice chatting with you.
Same to you!

uid1response.feedback: Thanks for the HIT!  I did my best and hope the data is useful!
